Qt Hldplugin version 3.0 contains bug fixes and new features.

There is a total of about 1250 changes by 60 individual contributors.

The most important changes are listed in this document. For a complete
list of changes, see the Git log for the Qt Hldplugin sources that
you can check out from the public Git repository. For example:

git clone git://gitorious.org/qt-hldplugin/qt-hldplugin.git
git log --cherry-pick --pretty=oneline v2.8.1..origin/3.0

General
   * Added -pluginpath command line argument for adding plugin search paths
   * Fixed "All templates" entry in "New" dialog (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9792)

Editing
   * Added option to close all files when deleted files for open editors
     are detected
   * Fixed issues with splitting when editor is not splittable (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-6827)
   * Added action for closing all editors except the visible ones (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9893)
   * Added support for changing case of entered values in snippets
     (:u :c :l modifiers like for custom wizards)
   * Fixed that proposal list would pop up again after it was dismissed with Esc key
     right after it opened

Managing and Building Projects
   * Fixed exit code that is shown for applications that are run in terminal
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9740)
   * Added support for ANSI colors in compile and application output
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-5956, QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9592)
   * Added support for renaming auto-detected kits, Qt versions, compilers and debuggers
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9787)

Compilers

Devices

QMake Projects
   * Fixed issues when using qtchooser (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9841)
   * Fixed issues with autosave files triggering reparses (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9957)
   * Fixed that run configurations were created for targets that are not built (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9549)
   * Fixed issue when renaming a file changes its MIME type (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9824)

CMake Projects
   * Added parser for CMake build errors
   * Fixed that build targets were not updated when CMakeLists.txt changes
   * Added support for a CMakeDeployment.txt file that defines deployment rules

Qbs Projects
   * Added code completion support for code generated from .ui files

Generic Projects

Debugging
   * Added Debuggers tab to Build & Run options
   * Pretty printers (Python based, GDB and LLDB)
      * Added QIPv6Address and support for IPv6 in QHostAddress
   * GDB
   * CDB
      * Fixed interrupting 32 bit processes from 64 bit Qt Hldplugin builds
   * LLDB
   * QML

Analyzer

C++ Support
   * Fixed finding usages of template classes and functions
   * Fixed support for namespace aliases inside blocks and functions (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-166)
   * Fixed support for class and enum definitions inside blocks and functions
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-3620, QTHLDPLUGINBUG-6013, QTHLDPLUGINBUG-8020)
   * Added code completion support for lambda calls (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9523)
   * Added graceful handling of Objective-C's @try, @catch and @throw statements
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9309)
   * Fixed completion for templates with template parameters inside namespace
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-8852)
   * Fixed handling of wide and UTF-n string literals
   * Added option to explicitly choose a project for a file, and add preprocessor directives
     specific to it (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9802, QTHLDPLUGINBUG-1249)
   * Fixed crash when resolving typedefs with templates (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10320)
   * Fixed crash when completing switch/case statement (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10366)
   * Fixed issues with showing type hierarchy (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9819)
   * Added "Optimize For Loop" refactoring action
   * Added "Extract Constant as Function Parameter" refactoring action
   * Added include hierarchy view in navigation side bar
   * Added list of potential destinations when doing "Follow Symbol" on
     virtual function calls (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9611)
   * Fixed "Follow Symbol" for operators (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-7485)
   * Added logic to avoid complete project reparses (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9730)
   * Added matching against fully qualified name in C++ related locator filters

Qt Quick Designer
   * Added imports editor
   * Fixed bread crumb bar for infile components

Qt Designer
   * Fixed "Go to slot" for form classes that are not part of a project (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9653)

Python Support

GLSL Support
   * Fixed crash (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10166)

Diff Viewer
   * Added button that switches between inline and side-by-side view (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10035)
   * Added syntax highlighting (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9580)

Version Control Systems
   * Fixed crash when reverting changes while commit editor is open (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10190)
   * Fixed colors in description in submit editor
   * Added VCS topic to window title
   * Fixed that user was asked about adding file to VCS even if it already
     was in VCS (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-2455)
   * Git
      * Added information about files with conflict when doing "git stash pop"
      * Added action for opening "git gui"
      * Added support for removing and renaming tags
      * Added support for setting remote tracking branch (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-8863)
      * Added disambiguation of branch names (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9700)
      * Fixed updating of log view from branches dialog (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9783)
      * Added support for cherry-picking top commit from a branch
      * Changed log to follow renames
      * Fixed that author data was discarded when commit window lost focus
      * Added support for "git reflog"
      * Added list of branches to header when showing commits
      * Fixed that cloning showed progress messages only after the
        operation was done (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-6565)
      * Added support for recursive clone
      * Added support for staging and unstaging chunks in unified diff editor (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-5875)
      * Fixed "Blame <commit>" and "Blame Parent" for renamed files
   * ClearCase

FakeVim
   * Added <C-W><C-V> shortcut for splitting editors
   * Fixed scrolling when using single character or single line movement

Platform Specific

Linux

Qt Support

QNX
   * Added check for existence of debug token and show error message in that case (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9103)
   * Added device auto-detection in "Add BlackBerry Device" wizard
   * Added support for NDKs with multiple target configurations

Android
   * Added error messages for incompatible devices to compile output (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9690)
   * Fixed browse button for OpenJDK location (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9706)
   * Fixed generated kit display name (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9865)
   * Fixed issues with Android virtual devices support
   * Added support for minimum and target SDK settings
   * Added target selector to manifest editor (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9682)
   * Improved the keystore and certificate dialog (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10061)
   * Made signing option independent of debug vs release builds (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10060)
   * Fixed signing with OpenJDK 7
   * Added support for Qt 5.2 deployment mechanism
   * Added editor for third-party libraries to deployment settings (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9849)

Remote Linux
   * Fixed ssh authentication for servers that don't allow non-interactive
     password authentication (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9568)

Bare Metal
   * Added experimental support for devices with only a gdbserver/openocd

